Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 10:46:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] perf: fix double lineOffset add, stale cache, debounce
 compose, paragraph memo

Core bugs fixed:
1. Double lineOffset add: Worker already added lineOffset to positions, then
   compose effect added it again. The add in Worker is moved out; Worker now
   returns paragraph-local coordinates (line=0-based). Only compose adds
   lineOffset.
2. Stale Worker cache: since lineOffset depended on previous paragraphs'
   totalLines, any paragraph insert invalidated lineOffset for all following
   paragraphs, but paraPosCache (keyed by paraId) was never refreshed.
   Now cache is paraId-stable because it holds local coords.
3. Compose effect never refired: deps had been stripped to [maxPerLine] via
   ref hacks to stop a previous infinite loop, which meant paraPosCache
   updates did not trigger recomposition. Restored [paraPosCache,
   debouncedDocument, baseMetrics.maxPerLine].

Performance:
- 40ms debounce on compose (batches rapid paraPosCache updates from Worker
  batch dispatch into one compose per burst).
- Paragraph-level segMap memo caches utf16Lens per paragraph so compose
  does not re-run codePointAt on 140k characters every pass.
- Worker dispatch no longer iterates doc to build offsetMap.

Typing-lag on 140k text:
- Before: ~70ms per compose x N Worker batches per keystroke burst.
- After:  ~50ms per compose x 1 per keystroke burst (post-debounce).

Follow-ups (not in this commit):
- Remove debouncedDocumentRef (no longer needed; compose reads state directly).
- Consider typed-array positions / segment-sliced charPositionsCache to push
  single-compose cost below 10ms on 140k text. Requires consumer-side changes
  in highlights/ghostHighlights/correctionHighlights/scrollToCaretPosition.
